  "session": "2026RS",
  "identifier": "HB 519",
  "title": "AN ACT relating to identity documents.",
  "abstract": "Create a new section of KRS 186.400 to 186.640  to define \"communication disorder\"; establish that at the time of application for an instruction permit, operator's license, or personal identification card a person may choose to have a notation on the document indicating that they have a communication disorder; direct that no fee shall be charged for the inclusion or removal of a notation; provide that a person may request removal of the notation; direct that the Department of Kentucky State Police shall implement training on interacting with persons who have a communication disorder; amend KRS 186.531 to conform; EFFECTIVE July 1, 2027.",
